{"source_key":"sha256-a74ceb5e1c9633ab993c14c11d587d71","record_index":1401,"record_hash":"sha256:66a5bf8e4682f5bd23ec224c0a6c2f13db135d43e2449f615cf4fa2628299ddc","timestamp":"2026-05-21T03:01:09.490Z","kind":"tool_call","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:custom_tool_call","role":null,"text":null,"tool_name":"apply_patch","tool_input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: [REDACTED:entropy].md\n@@\n Current handoff direction:\n \n - build generic agentlog primitives, not product-specific review/handoff APIs\n - no storage rewrite unless the current GitMeta shape cannot support the next\n   read command cleanly\n-- next planned slices are richer `sessions`, compact `timeline`, bounded\n-  `records`, then a workflow note or skill\n+- current read slices are richer `sessions`, compact `timeline`, and bounded\n+  `records`\n - keep the language as \"related\" evidence, not branch/session ownership\n - `timeline` may hydrate existing records internally, but should return compact\n   orientation data; full transcript records belong in bounded `records` output\n+\n+## Handoff Recovery Workflow\n+\n+Use the read commands as a narrowing funnel:\n+\n+1. Start from a target and find candidate sessions.\n+2. Open a compact timeline for the best candidate session.\n+3. Hydrate bounded records only for the turn that needs detail.\n+\n+Example:\n+\n+```sh\n+but agentlog sessions branch main --limit 5\n+but agentlog timeline <session-key> --limit 20\n+but agentlog records <session-key> --turn <turn-key> --limit 50\n+```\n+\n+The goal is orientation first, payload later. Do not start by dumping full\n+records for every related session; that loses the signal these commands are\n+trying to preserve.\n+\n+### Reading `sessions`\n+\n+Use `sessions` to answer \"which captured sessions are probably relevant to this\n+target?\"\n+\n+Supported targets:\n+\n+```sh\n+but agentlog sessions branch <branch-name-or-ref> --limit 5\n+but agentlog sessions review <review-id-or-key> --limit 5\n+but agentlog sessions change <change-id-or-key> --limit 5\n+```\n+\n+Important fields:\n+\n+- `session_key`: handle for follow-up reads.\n+- `latest_captured_at`: freshness signal.\n+- `record_count` and `turn_count`: rough size estimate before hydration.\n+- `related_turn_keys`: turns with direct target evidence.\n+- `match_evidence`: why the session was returned.\n+- `observed_targets`: branch/review/change keys observed in related turns.\n+- `latest_user_preview` and `latest_assistant_preview`: quick intent/result\n+  scan.\n+\n+Related sessions are sorted by latest activity. Treat this as relevance by\n+freshness, not proof of ownership.\n+\n+### Reading `timeline`\n+\n+Use `timeline` to answer \"what happened in this session, at turn granularity?\"\n+\n+```sh\n+but agentlog timeline <session-key> --limit 20\n+```\n+\n+Important fields:\n+\n+- `coverage`: how many turns were returned versus total turns.\n+- `turn_key`: handle for `records`.\n+- `turn_index`: stable order within the session.\n+- `capture_kind`: backfill or incremental.\n+- `record_count`: size of the turn before hydrating records.\n+- `source_record_index_range`: provider/source indexes covered by the turn.\n+- `observed_targets`: targets observed in that turn.\n+- `latest_user_preview` and `latest_assistant_preview`: compact orientation.\n+- `tool_counts`: tool call/result counts and tool names.\n+\n+Use the smallest timeline window that gives enough context. Increase `--limit`\n+when the latest window does not include the related turn or its immediate\n+setup.\n+\n+### Reading `records`\n+\n+Use `records` to answer \"what exactly happened inside this turn?\"\n+\n+```sh\n+but agentlog records <session-key> --turn <turn-key> --limit 50\n+```\n+\n+Important fields:\n+\n+- `coverage`: how many records were returned versus total records in the turn.\n+- `turn_record_index`: order within the turn.\n+- `source_record_index`: original provider/source index when available.\n+- `timestamp`, `kind`, `role`, `text`: message/tool orientation.\n+- `tool_name` and `tool_input`: tool details when present.\n+- `source_record`: redacted stored provider envelope for low-level debugging.\n+\n+`records` is intentionally bounded. Increase `--limit` only for a specific turn\n+after `timeline` shows that the extra detail is needed.\n+\n+### Agent Handoff Pattern\n+\n+For a handoff summary, capture:\n+\n+- the target used for discovery\n+- the chosen `session_key`\n+- the relevant `turn_key` values\n+- the latest user/assistant previews that explain intent and outcome\n+- record snippets only for the few turns that justify the next action\n+\n+Write conclusions in terms of observed evidence. Prefer \"session related to\n+branch X via turn Y\" over \"session for branch X\".\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-21T03:01:09.490Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}